title: Super Pocoyo
description: Today Pocoyo is Super Pocoyo - a superhero determined to rescue his friends from tight fixes - even when they don't need to be rescued.

title: Elly Spots
description: Elly is stricken with a case of the Elly Spots, and Pato and Pocoyo have to forsake their picnic to look after her. Once she is better, she makes it up to them.

title: Drawn to Sports with Hannah
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating young athletes from all over the country who are Drawn to Sports! Hannah competes in track and field.

title: The Beepers: The Visitor
description: The Beepers find the perfect groove after a new friend shreds a little too hard.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Dumbrella
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, have been traveling on the back of a truck in the rain for days. Charlie produces an umbrella to help his friend but unfortunately it's a "dumbrella" and it's looking to have some fun with them!

title: Do You Speak Dance/A New Spider in Town/Dollhouse Mates
description: "Maizie" keeps ignoring Lucas and Findley, but not only do they learn she has a cousin, they also learn a new skill!/ Lucas befriends a bright purple toy spider, and Findley gets jealous./ Lucas and Findley move into the dollhouse together.

title: Lost
description: Bing and Flop are in the park with Hoppity. What will happen when Bing finds some dog poo?

title: Top of the Titans: Best Love Songs
description: The Titans follow their heart with songs devoted to their greatest relationships: Beast Boy & Raven, Cyborg & Jinx and the Titans & Food.

title: Gryffindor v Hufflepuff
description: Dame Helen Mirren hosts the first episode of this epic TV event series. Over 4 episodes the Houses of Hogwarts will do battle to see which team knows the most about the wizarding world, featuring celebrity guests, actors from the original films and more Harry Potter Magic than you could find on a day trip to Diagon Alley. Tonight's match up sees the brave Gryffindors face the loyal Hufflepuffs for a guaranteed place in the grand finale.
originalseriesname: Harry Potter: Hogwarts Tournament of Houses

title: Clayton
description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Meet Cheetara
description: Cheetara is the coolest cat around! Not only is she so fast that she can outrun lightning, but so clever she can outsmart Mumm-Ra's evil plans! Villains don't stand a chance against Cheetara…well, unless Mumm-Ra uses his Doom Staff, then she might be in trouble.

title: Top of the Titans:  Raddest Songs
description: From "Booty Scooty" to "Sour Grapes" to "The Night Begins to Shine," Birdarang is here to count down the raddest music from Teen Titans Go!

title: Drawn to Change
description: Cartoon Network is Drawn to Change, and Craig of the Creek talks to Martin Luther King Junior's granddaughter Yolanda about how kids can change the world!

title: Having a Ball
description: Pocoyo and Pato are enjoying playing with their new ball. But all of a sudden, the ball takes on a life of its own, and Pocoyo and Pato have to chase it. Who's got the ball…? It's Baby Bird who just wants to play too!

title: Backyard Zoo/Caillou's Scavenger Hunt/Too Many Cooks/The Berry Patch
description: Caillou and Clementine and Leo make their own zoo in the backyard./When Julie comes over to babysit she announces that she's brought along a really fun game./Caillou's babysitter is late./Caillou spends a day strawberry picking.

title: Top of the Titans: Beast Boy & Cyborg Songs
description: Birdarang counts down the best musical moments from the raddest bros you know, Beast Boy and Cyborg. Waffles!

title: Meet Lion-O
description: Meet Lion-O and the Thundercats! After fleeing their home planet, the Thundercats find themselves stranded on Third Earth where they face the evil Mumm-Ra. But Lion-O is strong! He's tough! There's nothing he can't do! Except maybe open really big jars of cookies…

title: Flower Power
description: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden.

title: Lego DC Super Hero Girls: Brain Drain
description: Missing memories provide an intriguing mystery for everyone's favorite young female heroes in this all-new animated film.  When Supergirl, Wonder Woman, Batgirl, Harley Quinn, Bumblebee, Poison Ivy and Katana suddenly realize they cannot remember a single moment from their Monday at Super Hero High, the young Super Heroes spring into sleuthing action! Suspecting foul-play, they band together to retrace their steps and uncover the mystery of who exactly stole their memories - and, what nefarious plan might be afoot?

title: Drawn to Sports with Luke
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating young athletes from all over the country who are Drawn to Sports! Luke is passionate about running, jumping and climbing in Ninja Racing.

title: Caillou's Suitcase/Try, Try Again/The New Leaf/Happy New Year
description: Caillou's very excited about a family trip and decides to pack his own suitcase./Caillou has trouble learning to tie his shoelaces./Caillou, Grandpa and Dad go for a special hike in the woods./Caillou celebrates Chinese New Year.

title: Sarah
description: Darwin asks Sarah for a photo to put on the cover of the school yearbook. But when Sarah tries to help, things get a little sticky. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Top of the Titans: Dance Party!
description: Come correct because it's a Titans Dance Battle! Birdarang reviews the greatest dance songs in Teen Titans Go! history.

title: Caillou Goes to the Car Wash/Far Away Home/All You Can Eat/Caillou Stays Up Late
description: Caillou, Dad and Rosie take the car to the car wash./Caillou uses his imagination to turn the house into the setting for a desert expedition./Caillou and Mom are joining Clementine and her mom for a picnic./Caillou finds out his parents are having a grown-up party.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Big City Dancers
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, traveling on the back of a truck visit NYC where the rhythms of the city make Charlie wanna dance his little back porch off. Frank … not so much. But when you go far enough into the city, anything can happen.

title: Teachers
description: When Darwin asks his friends which teacher deserves to be on the yearbook cover, they struggle to find a single worthy candidate! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Drawn To Expression!
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating queer youth and families in the LGBTQIA+ community that radiate joy, pride, and inclusivity. We are championing the ways these kids and families form connections to their authentic selves by expressing their creativity and queer identity through their art.

title: We Baby Bears: BHA Bha Song
description: We Baby Bears follows baby bear brothers Grizz, Panda, and Ice Bear as they journey in a magical box to fantastic different worlds in search of their perfect home.

title: Alan
description: Darwin wants to put Alan on the cover of the school yearbook - but Alan's apparent modesty gets in the way. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Big Rumble
description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

title: The Beepers: Funky Time
description: The Beepers play with tempo and learn that adapting to change can be…sweaty.

title: Lightning Bugs Sylvester
description: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

title: Win It or Bin It
description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

title: We Baby Bears Official Trailer: New Series
description: These baby bears are searching for a brand new home, and they're off to fantastical worlds and new adventures along the way. Watch the official trailer for We Baby Bears, the brand new show from the creators of We Bare Bears, coming to Cartoon Network in 2022.

title: Alpha Bodies
description: Cartoonito presents Alpha Bodies! It's time to use our bodies to make every letter of the alphabet, from A to Z, but one over-eager letter keeps getting ahead of itself.

title: Banana Joe
description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Drawn to Sports with Olivia
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating young athletes from all over the country who are Drawn to Sports! Olivia is a tennis player who is also passionate about art.

title: DC Super Hero Girls: Super Hero High
description: Supergirl arrives at Super Hero High and struggles to learn to control her new powers. Meanwhile, the Junior Detective Club investigates a mysterious rash of security breaches centered around the teleportation Boom Tubes.

title: Caillou's Teddy Shirt/Caillou Meets Robbie/The Pinata/Caillou's Promise
description: Caillou's favorite shirt has teddy bears on it./Caillou introduces himself to another little boy at the park./Caillou can't wait for the mailman to deliver his invitation to his friend Xavier's party./Caillou learns about keeping promises.

title: Hello Around the World
description: Cartoonito presents Hello Around the World! All across the globe, friends greet each other in lots of different languages. Watch along and discover some of the many ways to say "Hello," around the world and beyond!

title: Excalibear
description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

title: The Beepers: Spotlight
description: When a spotlight gives everyone a chance to solo, a shy Beeper discovers the courage to shine.

title: Drawn To Rhythm: Lorenzo
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Hispanic Heritage Month with another installment of "Drawn To" that showcases kids who honor their Hispanic and Latino heritage as they are drawn to rhythm. In this piece, Lorenzo tells us about his passion for reggaetón music and soccer.

title: Drawn To Juneteenth: Julian
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Juneteenth! Juneteenth commemorates the end of slavery with celebrations that take place every year on June 19th! This holiday recognizes the day that all slaves were free in the U.S.! We are recognizing those who are dedicated to making this special holiday known as they are Drawn to...Juneteenth!

title: Meet Mumm-ra and the Mutants
description: The Thundercats have met their match with the evil, undead Mumm-ra! He and the bumbling Mutants have made it their goal to stop the Thundercats by any means necessary, but of course the Thundercats have other plans!

title: Modern-ish Stone Age Family
description: The Bears are invited to live with a family of cavemen but things get rocky when the bears teach the family about television.

title: The Chef's Challenge
description: Craig and his friends find themselves entering a cooking battle for a piece of the cube.

title: World Cup
description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

title: The Quick Name
description: Craig tries to rid himself of a bad nickname.

title: The Snake Dance
description: When Mush-Mush and Chep lose Lilit's flying disc down a snake tunnel, he is confident he can get it back. All animals love Chep and no one knows more about snakes than he does. But this snake is not to be messed with! When they finally sneak into the snake tunnel, they learn why the snake has been acting so strangely…

title: Drawn to Ancestry
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Asian-American Pacific Islander Heritage Month and recognizing amazing kids who learn from their elders to pave their future! We're honoring the special bond between kids and their grandparents as they are Drawn To Ancestry.

title: Drawn To Juneteenth: Ms. Opal
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Juneteenth! Juneteenth commemorates the end of slavery with celebrations that take place every year on June 19th! This holiday recognizes the day that all slaves were free in the U.S.! We are recognizing those who are dedicated to making this special holiday known as they are Drawn to...Juneteenth!

title: Picnic
description: It's picnic time! Bing and Flop are getting ready to have a picnic, but will they remember to bring everything they need?

title: Up Up and Away
description: Our friends are playing with a model airplane which shoots off up into space. They go on an adventure to retrieve the beloved toy, encountering some friendly, bendy aliens along the way.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Eye Spy
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, are traveling on the back of a truck from Montana to Utah. Charlie wants to play a game of Eye Spy. He finds more and more obvious objects for Frank to spy but Frank isn't quite getting the hang of it. Yet!

title: Drawn To Rhythm: Jayleen
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Hispanic Heritage Month with another installment of "Drawn To" that showcases kids who honor their Hispanic and Latino heritage as they are drawn to rhythm. In this piece, Jayleen shows us some of the eight different dance styles she can do, including bachata and cumbia.

title: Overnight Stop
description: Percy feels anxious about spending a night away from home during an overnight delivery with Thomas and Nia.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Drawn To Juneteenth: Miss Juneteenth
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating Juneteenth! Juneteenth commemorates the end of slavery with celebrations that take place every year on June 19th! This holiday recognizes the day that all slaves were free in the U.S.! We are recognizing those who are dedicated to making this special holiday known as they are Drawn to...Juneteenth!

title: Super Screen Cleaners
description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Meet Panthro
description: Panthro may be the strongest cat on Third Earth, but one of his biggest strengths is that he can fix anything!  And the rest of the Thundercats break enough stuff to really put his skills to the test, but it's nothing a pro like Panthro can't handle.

title: Carrie
description: Darwin sets out to find a photo of Carrie for the cover of the school yearbook - but they end up reminiscing about all their past spooky shenanigans. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Top of the Titans: Best Rivals
description: From Trigon to Terra to Darkseid, Robin counts down the worst of the worst: the greatest villains to ever challenge the Teen Titans!

title: DC Super Hero Girls: Intergalactic Games
description: Super Hero High is facing off against Korugar Academy in the Intergalactic Games, but Lena Luthor takes advantage of the gathering of supers to enact her villainous plan.

title: A Surprise for Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo's friends decide to give him a surprise party - simply to show him how much they love him.

title: The Birthday That Wasn't
description: Dibble misunderstands the Bears' intentions when they secretly make a plush toy Whiffle for her "Un-birthday." Thinking it's real and that the Bears love it more than they love her, she steals it and plans to leave it in the forest. She has second thoughts and returns her "rival" to her friends, only to learn that it's a gift to show their love for her.

title: A Surprise for Mommy/Caillou Misses Sarah/T-Shirt Trouble/A Helping Hand
description: Dad gets a professional photo of Caillou and Rosie./Caillou's friend Sarah is going away on a trip for two whole weeks./Caillou's brand new T-shirt is ruined by grape juice./Caillou and Grandma, along with Rover the dog, spend a day at a retirement home.

title: Bird Call
description: Chanterelle has built a whistle that can reproduce the most beautiful sound of the forest: the one of the Nightingale. When the whistle disappears, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit soon discover that it has been stolen by a beetle. In order to finally hear what a real Nightingale sounds like, they'll have to get it back!

title: Drawn to Making it Happen with Sidney Keys
description: Cartoon Network celebrates Black History Month with Sidney Keys III, a 15-year-old rising entrepreneur and the founder and CEO of "Books n Bros," an African American literature book club for male youth ages 7-13 years old. Focused on promoting literacy among young Black boys and introducing them to positive representation in literature, Keys' advocacy is paving the way for change by creating a place for boys to be mentored by their "Big Bros" and connect over a shared love for reading.

title: Drawn to Community
description: Cartoon Network is celebrating awesome kids who are giving back and making a difference to those around them. CN is recognizing extraordinary girls who are channeling their interests into outreach as they are Drawn to… Community!

title: Lucas We Have a Problem/Egg-Scuse Me/Pokey Dokey
description: Lucas helps Bodhi fulfill her dream of touching a star./ Lucas finds an egg and decides to take care of it. But he learns that responsibility is hard./ When Avocado loses her beloved toy, Lucas and Findley are determined to cheer her up.
